quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  8,9,"Recall: you<sup>pl </sup>crying for help from your Lord, so He responded to you, “I am surely reinforcing you with one thousand angels in succession{1}.”",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Nafie’, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “…one thousand angels succeeding one another.”
  8,10,"And Allah only made it as a glad tiding, and so that your hearts should become serene thereby, for support{1}is only from Allah; indeed, Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used for support is <i>nasr </i>which also means victory.
